Materials
1. Garlic
2. Honey
3. Garlic Press
4. Weigh Boats 
5. Scale
6. Autoclave
7. Erlenmeyer Flask
8. Stir bar
9. Vacuum Filtration System
10. Mueller Hinton Agar
11. Plates 
12. Fresh Culture of Staphylococcus Aureus
13. Sterile Swabs
14. Sterile PBS
15. Vancomycin Disk
16. Sterile forcepts 
17. Incubator 
18. Ruler 
Methods
1. Make 100x stock solutions of water + garlic and water + honey 
2. Weigh out agar and combine with appropriate amount of water and stir bar in erlenmeyer flasks for the different treatment groups
3. Place this mixture in an autoclave and run a liquid sterilizing cycle 
4. Once cycle is done take the agar out and place on stir plates to allow to cool
5. Once cooled add the garlic and honey stock solutions to their appropriate flask to make different concentrations of the agar plates
6. Pour this mixture into plates and let the agar set then immediately refrigerate.
7. Grow a fresh culture of staph aureus over night
8. Take a swab and pick up a colony of the staph aureus and mix it into a tube with sterile PBS
9. Then take fresh sterile swabs, dip into the pbs, streak the agar plate and repeat this step for all of the plates.
10. On half of the plates take forceps and place a vancomycin disk in the middle
11. Place these plates in an incubator for 29 hours to allow for growth and diffusion of the mix
12. Once the time is completed pull the plates out of the incubator and use a ruler to meausure the zone of inhibitions.

